## Spring Boot — Flavor-Specific Notes

### Architecture

Spring Boot 3+ with Gradle Kotlin DSL. Java 21. Layered architecture.

### Layer Structure
```
src/main/java/{{PACKAGE}}/
├── config/        # Spring configuration, security, CORS
├── controller/    # REST endpoints (@RestController)
├── service/       # Business logic (@Service)
├── repository/    # Data access (@Repository)
└── model/         # Domain entities, DTOs
```

### Commands

| Command | Purpose | Speed |
|---------|---------|-------|
| `./gradlew bootRun` | Start dev server | ~10s |
| `./gradlew test` | Run all tests | ~30s |
| `./gradlew build` | Full build with tests | ~45s |
| `./gradlew bootJar` | Create executable JAR | ~30s |
| `./gradlew dependencyCheckAnalyze` | OWASP vulnerability scan | ~60s |

### Key Conventions

- **No raw SQL in controllers** — all data access through `@Repository`
- **Validation** — use `@Valid` + Jakarta validation annotations on DTOs
- **Profiles** — `dev` for local, `prod` for production. Set via `SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE`
- **No hardcoded credentials** — use environment variables or Spring config
- **Test naming** — `MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult` pattern
- **Actuator** — `/actuator/health`, `/actuator/info`, `/actuator/metrics` enabled

### Docker

```bash
docker compose up          # Start app (+ optional DB)
docker compose up --build  # Rebuild and start
```
